<tal:root
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  omit-tag="">

<div class="portlet" id="portlet-requires-subscription"
     tal:condition="context/commercial_subscription_is_due">
  <img style="padding-top: 1em; float: right" alt="" src="/@@/warning-large" />
  <h2>
    Purchasing a Subscription is Required
  </h2>
  <div tal:condition="context/commercial_subscription/date_expires | nothing">
    <strong>Current subscription expires
    <span 
     tal:replace="context/commercial_subscription/date_expires/fmt:displaydate"
    />.
    </strong>
  </div>
  <div>
    The licensing of your project does not qualify for free
    hosting. You have two options to continue using Launchpad
    for this project.
    <ul>
      <li><a href="+purchase-subscription">Purchase a subscription</a></li>
      <li><a href="mailto:feedback@launchpad.net">Contact us</a>
          about changing your license.
      </li>
    </ul>
    To qualify for free hosting, the project's licensing must meet the
    following requirements:
    <ul>
      <li>Must include source code.</li>
      <li>Must allow modification and distribution of modified copies under
          the same license.</li>
      <li>Must allow redistribution.</li>
      <li>Must not require royalty payments or any other fee for
          redistribution or modification.</li>
      <li>Must allow these rights to be passed on along with the software.</li>
      <li>Must not discriminate against persons, groups or against fields
          of endeavour.</li>
      <li>Must not be distributed under a license specific to Ubuntu.</li>
      <li>Must not contaminate other software licenses.</li>
    </ul>

    <a href="http://www.ubuntu.com/community/ubuntustory/licensing">
      View Licensing Policies
    </a>
  </div>
</div>
</tal:root>
